# This is a placeholder file for the demo video
# For the demo to work properly, replace this with an actual MP4 video file
# You can use any video file with objects to detect (people, cars, etc.)

# Recommended video sources:
# 1. Download a sample video from: https://sample-videos.com/
# 2. Use your own video file with moving objects
# 3. Use a webcam by running: ./run_demo.sh 0

# Video requirements:
# - Format: MP4, AVI, or any OpenCV-supported format
# - Resolution: 640x480 or higher
# - Content: Contains objects like people, cars, or other detectable items
# - Duration: At least 10 seconds for good demonstration

# To create a test video with ffmpeg (if available):
# ffmpeg -f lavfi -i testsrc=duration=30:size=640x480:rate=30 -c:v libx264 demo_video.mp4
